The product Bernoulli distribution `Ber(u, p)` is defined as the measure on `Set ι` such that each element `i ∈ u` belongs to a random set with probability `p`, and elements `i ∉ u` never belong to it. The distribution `Ber(u, p)` is constructed as an infinite product of Bernoulli distributions on the elements of `u`.

