```tactics
variable (u p) in
/-- The binomial distribution with parameter `p` on the set `u : Set V` is the measure on `Set V`
such that each element of `u` is taken with probability `p`, and the elements outside of `u` are
never taken. -/
noncomputable def bernoulliOn : Measure (Set ι) :=
  .comap (fun s i ↦ i ∈ s) <| infinitePi fun i ↦
    toNNReal p • dirac (i ∈ u) + toNNReal (σ p) • dirac False
```

This defines the Bernoulli measure on the set of subsets of `ι`. The measure is constructed using `infinitePi` to create a product measure, where each element `i` is included with probability `p` if `i ∈ u`, and excluded with probability `1 - p`. The `comap` is used to lift this measure to the space of subsets.

```tactics
