```

This provides the notation `Ber(u, p)` for our Bernoulli measure.

```tactics
instance : IsProbabilityMeasure Ber(u, p) :=
  MeasurableEquiv.setOf.symm.measurableEmbedding.isProbabilityMeasure_comap <| .of_forall fun P ↦
    ⟨{a | P a}, rfl⟩
```

This proves that `Ber(u, p)` is a probability measure. The construction using `infinitePi` and `comap` ensures that this is a probability measure on the space of subsets.

```tactics
