@[simp] lemma bernoulliOn_one : Ber(u, 1) = dirac u := by simp [bernoulliOn_eq_map]
```

This proves that when `p = 1`, the Bernoulli measure `Ber(u, 1)` is concentrated at the set `u`. This makes sense because if each element is included with probability 1, then the resulting set is exactly `u`.

