This lemma is saying that if `X` and `Y` are equal almost surely with respect to `P`, then `X` is `p`-Bernoulli on `u` if and only if `Y` is `p`-Bernoulli on `u`. This follows directly from the fact that having a certain distribution is preserved under almost sure equality.

