If `1_{X}(i)` is Bernoulli `p`, then `1 - 1_{X}(i)` is Bernoulli `σ p` (where `σ` is the complement operation on probabilities). Since the distribution of `X` is a product measure, the distribution of `u \ X` will also be a product measure, specifically `Ber(u, σ p)`.

